f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Binance calculates BONK/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium index. The funding rate is capped at ±2% per funding interval to prevent extreme payments. When the perpetual price trades above spot (positive funding), long positions pay shorts; when below spot (negative funding), shorts pay longs. Payments are automatically debited or credited to account balances without requiring manual intervention."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BONK","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's status as a popular Solana meme coin creates significant price volatility and frequent funding rate imbalances on Binance. The pair's mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage while maintaining enough volatility to generate meaningful funding rate spreads. Binance's dominant market share in BONK trading ensures that funding rates here often lead other exchanges, creating cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK/USDT funding rates on Binance typically range from -0.5% to +1.2% per 8-hour period, with extreme spikes during meme coin rallies reaching +2% caps. During Solana ecosystem pumps, BONK often sustains positive funding for 3-5 consecutive cycles as retail demand drives perpetual premiums. Bear market periods show more balanced funding with frequent negative rates as short interest increases. The pair exhibits stronger correlation with SOL/USDT funding patterns than with other meme coins, reflecting its Solana ecosystem ties."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage works effectively when Binance BONK funding rates diverge significantly from OKX or Bybit rates, often by 0.3%+ during high volatility periods. Calendar spread arbitrage using different expiry futures becomes viable when funding annualizes above 100% APR. Delta-neutral strategies combining BONK perpetuals with SOL positions can exploit correlation breakdowns during ecosystem-specific news events. Market makers can capture funding payments while providing liquidity through automated market making strategies that maintain delta-neutral exposure."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's meme coin status creates elevated liquidation risks due to sudden 20-40% price swings that can wipe out leveraged positions within minutes. Funding rate strategies require careful position sizing as Binance's auto-deleveraging system may close positions during extreme market stress. Solana network congestion can impact BONK deposits/withdrawals, creating settlement risks for cross-exchange arbitrage strategies. Regulatory uncertainty around meme coins adds delisting risk, though Binance's $1B+ insurance fund provides some protection against exchange-level failures."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"What is the maximum funding rate for BONK/USDT on Binance?","answer":"Binance caps BONK/USDT funding rates at ±2% per 8-hour interval (±6% daily). This prevents extreme funding payments that could destabilize the perpetual contract during high volatility periods common with meme coins."},{"question":"How does BONK funding compare to other Solana ecosystem tokens on Binance?","answer":"BONK typically shows higher funding rate volatility than SOL or RAY due to its meme coin nature and retail-heavy trading base. However, it often follows SOL's directional funding trends during broader Solana ecosystem moves or network events."},{"question":"Can I use BNB to reduce fees on BONK/USDT perpetual trades?","answer":"Yes, holding BNB provides a 25% discount on BONK/USDT perpetual futures fees, reducing maker fees from 0.02% to 0.015% and taker fees from 0.05% to 0.0375%. This significantly improves net returns for high-frequency funding rate strategies."},{"question":"What happens if BONK funding rates hit the 2% cap repeatedly?","answer":"When funding hits the cap multiple times, it signals extreme market imbalance. Binance may implement additional risk controls like increased margin requirements or temporary trading restrictions. Sustained capped funding often precedes major price corrections in meme coins."}]}]
